  "prompt": "Do snakes eat penguins?",
  "response": "Generally, snakes do not eat penguins. Penguins are primarily found in the Southern Hemisphere, particularly in Antarctica, while most snake species are found in warmer climates and different habitats. There are some larger snake species, like anacondas or certain pythons, that can eat birds, but encounters between snakes and penguins are very rare due to their differing habitats. In some unusual circumstances, such as in captivity or specific geographical overlaps, it might be possible, but it is not a common or typical predator-prey relationship.",
